# Axis 21 — one-shot violation diagnostic

A plain effect has a one-shot continuation. The first `resume` claims it; the
second must abort the run with the stable structured diagnostic. The print is an
outer suffix and therefore must produce no stdout after the rejection.

```scalascript
effect One:
  def op(): Int

val result = handle(One.op()) {
  case One.op(resume) => resume(1) + resume(2)
}
println(s"suffix: $result")
```
